<div class="container py-5">
    <h1>Our Breeder Operations</h1>

    <p>At our farm, everything starts with the breeder stock. Healthy, high-quality breeders are the cornerstone of sustainable poultry farming. We carefully select our breeder birds based on genetics, health, and productivity, ensuring that every chick produced meets our rigorous standards. Our breeders are not only valuable for their genetics but also for their welfare. Each bird is treated with care, housed in spacious, well-ventilated environments, and given diets specifically formulated for breeder health.</p>

    <h2>Selective Breeding</h2>
    <p>Our selective breeding program is designed to produce strong, resilient, and productive offspring. We monitor lineage and performance metrics to make informed breeding decisions. By selecting the best birds for reproduction, we maintain the integrity of our flock and enhance productivity. This careful selection process ensures that the next generation of poultry is healthy, hardy, and well-suited for our farm environment.</p>

    <h2>Housing and Environmental Control</h2>
    <p>Breeders are housed in facilities designed to maximize comfort and minimize stress. Proper ventilation, temperature control, and lighting cycles mimic natural conditions to support reproductive performance. Nesting boxes, perches, and areas for movement are carefully arranged to encourage natural behaviors and reduce stress-induced issues.</p>

    <h2>Nutrition for Optimal Fertility</h2>
    <p>Breeder birds require precise nutrition to maintain health and ensure high fertility rates. Our diets are formulated with the right balance of proteins, vitamins, minerals, and essential amino acids. Feed is provided in measured portions to prevent waste while ensuring each bird receives adequate nutrition. Clean, fresh water is always available to support hydration and metabolic health.</p>

    <h2>Egg Collection and Incubation</h2>
    <p>Eggs are collected carefully multiple times a day to maintain cleanliness and prevent damage. Each egg is labeled and tracked, ensuring full traceability. Our incubation process is highly controlled, with strict monitoring of temperature, humidity, and turning frequency. By maintaining precise incubation conditions, we achieve high hatch rates and healthy, vigorous chicks ready for our farm operations.</p>

    <h2>Health Management and Biosecurity</h2>
    <p>Regular health checks, vaccinations, and strict biosecurity protocols ensure our breeders remain healthy. Staff are trained to recognize early signs of illness and to respond immediately. Preventive care reduces the need for medications and promotes natural immunity, ensuring breeders remain productive throughout their lifespan.</p>

    <h2>Why Our Breeder Operations Matter</h2>
    <p>Investing in breeder operations is investing in the future of our farm. Healthy breeders lead to high-quality chicks, which translate into healthier flocks and better products for our customers. By maintaining rigorous standards at this foundational stage, we ensure that all subsequent farm operations meet our quality, welfare, and productivity goals.</p>

    <p>Our commitment to breeder excellence reflects our belief that poultry farming is both a science and an ethical responsibility. We aim not only to produce quality poultry but also to set a standard for how breeders should be cared for across the industry.</p>
